headline: General Electric and United Nuclear Agree to Consent Decree for Cleanup of Uranium Mine Waste
summary: General Electric and United Nuclear have agreed to a U.S. consent decree requiring an estimated $63 million cleanup of uranium mine waste at sites in New Mexico and the Navajo Nation.
